text: Mount Tagubud also called Mount Pandadagsaan or White Peak is the highest mountain in the province of Davao de Oro in the Philippines with an elevation of above sea level. Located in New Bataan Davao de Oro, Davao Region in the island of Mindanao Philippines, Mount Tagubud is the source of the Agusan River. ==References== Category:Mountains of the Philippines Category:Landforms of Davao de Oro
title: Mount Tagubud
